        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Doctor: expose sandbox registry findings",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Exposes legacy sandbox registry files as structured doctor health findings.\n- Adds dry-run repair effects for migrate, remove-empty, and quarantine registry-file outcomes.\n- Keeps the existing doctor:sandbox legacy run path as the only real mutating sandbox registry migration path for normal doctor / doctor --fix.\n- Declares the structured check inline on the existing ordered doctor contribution, so this PR does not add another core registry entry.\n\nThis is intentionally the small sandbox registry slice from the older doctor repair stack. It does not migrate sandbox image builds, namespace probes, Docker checks, or plugin-sensitive doctor rules.\n\n## Stack\n\nStacked on #86627. The only new sandbox commit in this PR is 622b8d6731; the sandbox delta is 4 files.\n\n## Validation\n\n- oxfmt check on doctor-sandbox and doctor-health-contributions files\n- oxlint on doctor-sandbox and doctor-health-contributions files\n- Vitest: src/commands/doctor-sandbox.warns-sandbox-enabled-without-docker.test.ts and src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.test.ts, 2 files, 40 tests\n- tsgo core: node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p tsconfig.core.json --noEmit --incremental false --pretty false\n- tsgo test: node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.core.test.json --noEmit --incremental false --pretty false\n- git diff --check\n- codex review --commit HEAD: clean, no actionable correctness issues\n",
